<emphasis id="B926D14F094BB215EC95FD6B212B48E6" bold="true" box="[151,288,695,719]" pageId="31" pageNumber="482">FIGURE 36.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094BB215ED24FD64223F48F9" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[294,564,696,720]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="482" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094BB215ED24FD64223F48F9" box="[294,564,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="482">Cryptocentroides arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Oman: Hasik.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2D5DD5094BB215EC95F8BF259F4D89" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541643" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541643/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="482" startId="31.[151,250,1891,1915]" targetBox="[151,1436,744,1868]" targetPageId="31">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094BB215EC95F8BF259F4D89" blockId="31.[151,1437,1891,1952]" pageId="31" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094BB215EC95F8BF212B4D55" bold="true" box="[151,288,1891,1916]" pageId="31" pageNumber="482">FIGURE 37.</emphasis>
Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094BB215EDF7F8B8230F4D55" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[501,772,1892,1916]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="482" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094BB215EDF7F8B8230F4D55" box="[501,772,1892,1916]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="482">Cryptocentroides arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Oman with three new locality records in the Wadis adjacent to the coastal area of the Arabian Sea. Pink: Southwestern Arabian Coast, green: Oman Mountains, and yellow: Arabian Interior.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0974B22AECC5FF4A251E4BA0" blockId="32.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AECC5FF4A21AB4A99" bold="true" box="[199,416,150,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Short description:</emphasis>
Comparing with eastern Australian species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0974B22AEF94FF4B24124A98" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[918,1049,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AEF94FF4B24124A98" box="[918,1049,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">C. arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from its congener 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0974B22AEC95FF67211B4AFD" baseAuthorityName="Seale" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[151,272,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AEC95FF67211B4AFD" box="[151,272,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having upper edge of operculum level with that of eye (vs. upper edge of eye above that of operculum), distance between lower edge of eye and upper jaw long and curved (vs. short and straight), posterior edge of preoperculum bent forward (vs. straight), soft and spinous parts of dorsal fin slightly separated (vs. closely connected), caudal fin pointed (vs. rounded), dorsal, pectoral and caudal fins yellowish, head and body with no spots, double dark bands on body, with zigzag shape (vs all fins with blueish colour, different sizes of blue spots distributed over head and body, dark bars on body straight and obliquely located) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0974B22AEFB6FEB3243F4BA0" author="Seale, A." box="[948,1076,367,393]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" pagination="491 - 543" refId="ref25165" refString="Seale, A. (1910) New species of Philippine fishes. Philippine Journal of Science A, 4, 491 - 543." type="journal article" year="1910">Seale 1910</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0974B22AE842FEB325034BA0" author="Jawad, L. A. &amp; Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Fricke, R." box="[1088,1288,367,393]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" pagination="7 - 12" refId="ref24252" refString="Jawad, L. A., Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Fricke, R. (2021) Discovery of an established population of the Arabian Goby Cryptocentroides arabicus (Gmelin, 1789) in a brackish water environment in Oman. Bulletin of Fish Biology, 20, 7 - 12." type="journal article" year="2021">
Jawad 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AE88FFEB324B54BA0" box="[1165,1214,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60974B22AECC5FE4E24644BF8" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0974B22AECC5FE4E24644BF8" blockId="32.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AECC5FE4E21684B85" bold="true" box="[199,355,402,428]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Distribution:</emphasis>
Red Sea; northwestern Indian Ocean: Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF0974B22AEF6FFE4F23A14B84" box="[877,938,403,429]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Aden</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0974B22AEFE3FE4F243C4B84" box="[993,1079,403,429]" name="Yemen" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Socotra</collectingCountry>
to Persian Gulf. Occurs in very shallow water, living in a burrow in sediment. Probably associated with alpheid shrimp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60974B22AECC5FE07216C48E4" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0974B22AECC5FE07220548AC" blockId="32.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AECC5FE0721364BDC" bold="true" box="[199,317,475,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Remarks:</emphasis>
An established population of the Arabian Goby 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0974B22AEF68FE07249D4BDC" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[874,1174,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AEF68FE07249D4BDC" box="[874,1174,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Cryptocentroides arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was discovered in one brackish water habitat (Al Bahayes), located in the inland water bodies of 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0974B22AEFD5FE2324104830" box="[983,1051,511,537]" name="Oman" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Oman</collectingCountry>
adjacent to the shore of the 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0974B22AE95AFE2325974830" box="[1368,1436,511,537]" name="Oman" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Oman</collectingCountry>
Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0974B22AECCCFDFF219D4814" author="Jawad, L. A. &amp; Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Fricke, R." box="[206,406,547,573]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" pagination="7 - 12" refId="ref24252" refString="Jawad, L. A., Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Fricke, R. (2021) Discovery of an established population of the Arabian Goby Cryptocentroides arabicus (Gmelin, 1789) in a brackish water environment in Oman. Bulletin of Fish Biology, 20, 7 - 12." type="journal article" year="2021">
Jawad 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AED1EFDFF21464814" box="[284,333,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we confirm its presence in four other localities (Hasik, Mugsil, Taqa and Wadi Shab), located in the inland water bodies of 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0974B22AEE3BFD9B22764848" box="[569,637,583,609]" name="Oman" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Oman</collectingCountry>
adjacent to the shore of the Arabian Sea (Hasik, Mugsil, Taqa) and the 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0974B22AEC95FDB720D048AC" box="[151,219,619,645]" name="Oman" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Oman</collectingCountry>
Sea (Wadi Shab) (
<figureCitation id="136911D80974B22AEDAFFDB7220948AC" box="[429,514,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,744,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-29@31.[151,1436,744,1868]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 37. Distribution map of Cryptocentroides arabicus in Oman with three new locality records in the Wadis adjacent to the coastal area of the Arabian Sea. Pink: Southwestern Arabian Coast, green: Oman Mountains, and yellow: Arabian Interior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541643" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541643/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
